A curious, clownish scientist's take: expect a compressed marine layer with inland warmth and coastal fog today, hazardous long‑period southerly swell with sneaker waves and strong rip currents through Wednesday, then a late‑week trough bringing cooler, gusty winds and patchy coastal drizzle Saturday — Чую, что скоро развергнутся хляби небесные! — largely unchanged from yesterday though winds and small‑craft advisories tighten later in the week.